Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.05,0:00:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kirin's Horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.05,0:00:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found by Advisor Suzuki Jirokichi inside\Na mountain temple on a Kirin statue....
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a horn made of amber.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After hearing the news, that grandiose\NKaitou Kid dispatched his calling card.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.53,0:00:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The advisor invited us Detective Boys,\Nwho he believes Kid cannot disguise as...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.03,0:00:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with a TV station's live broadcasting crew\Nto capture Kaitou Kid with great enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.29,0:00:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kirin statue was hidden in the central pillar of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to reveal it, four keys need to be inserted into\Nthe pedestals' keyholes in each of the four corners...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.63,0:00:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And must be turned all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.22,0:00:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, come get it if you dare, Kaitou Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.06,0:00:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here, right now, I'm gonna catch you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.92,0:01:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.82,0:01:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.59,0:01:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,The vanishing treasure and Kaitou Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.51,0:01:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,Only the Detective Boys will seek them out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.80,0:01:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fscy120\fscx120\fad(100,0)\bord0.1}Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.30,0:01:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fscy120\fscx120\fad(0,0)\bord0.1}The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.22,0:01:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fscy120\fscx120\fad(0,50)\bord0.1}His name is: Detective {\t(1550,1551,\shad0\1c&H4331B1&)}Conan{\1c&H6AE8FA&}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.90,0:03:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.94,0:03:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Close it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.65,0:03:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.95,0:03:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, if the four pedestal keys\Naren't turned at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.25,0:03:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one will be able to see the Kirin statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So long as that guy doesn't steal the keys\Nfrom me and split himself into four people...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll have no means of stealing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.18,0:03:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the creator of this device is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.35,0:03:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, the Master of Tricks from the Bakumatsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.93,0:03:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Samizu Kichiemon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.18,0:03:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's writing on the base of the pillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.94,0:03:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One who desires to acquire Kirin without depending on the\Ncorrect method must devote themselves to changing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Samizu Kichiemon," it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you figure out the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.37,0:03:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.54,0:03:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's all right so long as I have these four keys in my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.25,0:04:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Optimistic old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.17,0:04:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we assume that guy has three accomplices here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.17,0:04:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that all he needs to do is cut the\Nlights and steal the keys for an easy heist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.30,0:04:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if Kid were to tamper with these hastily affixed\Nlights, it seems the power would instantly go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.56,0:04:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.98,0:04:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he'd instantly have cut off the pedestal's electrical current too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be a relief if I could have someone guard the four\Npedestals even when the lights go out, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.57,0:04:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't know if my subordinates have\Nbeen switched with Kid's underlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't trust those three from the TV crew either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.41,0:04:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there was just one keyhole, I could guard it by myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.21,0:04:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Ayumi and the others will guard them for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.80,0:04:52.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid has no way to disguise as us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the ones you can rely on the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.43,0:05:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, if just the four of us managed to protect the\Ntreasure from Kid, we can rub it in Edogawa-kun's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.98,0:05:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.98,0:05:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you touch the pedestals before the\Npower is shut off, you'll get shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.53,0:05:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as we don't mess up the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the beeps, the power will turn off to the\Norder of green, red, white, and black, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, don't get confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, it's just ten minutes before Kid's announced time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.67,0:05:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will Kid really show up at this mountain temple\Nwhere the Detective Boys are lying in wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.05,0:05:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, let's all go catch Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.68,0:05:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun and the others are really on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.10,0:05:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you go there too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.27,0:05:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Jirokichi rejected us over the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.86,0:05:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This time I'm only inviting children.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.94,0:05:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"No one that Kid can disguise himself as!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.15,0:05:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.78,0:05:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a five minute break!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.70,0:06:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be going on standby three minutes\Nbefore showtime, so I'll be counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.95,0:06:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.83,0:06:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.33,0:06:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we'll go on standby too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.67,0:06:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are you guys going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To guard the pedestals!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.92,0:06:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question is whether or not you'll guard the keys, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the keys nailed to the wall like that, that guy can do nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's my victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.02,0:06:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blackout?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.82,0:06:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get flustered!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blackout is to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rain and wind...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.87,0:06:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone opened the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you getting this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.20,0:06:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but in this darkness, there's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.00,0:06:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the audio?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're picking it up for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:04.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.10,0:07:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pillar!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.32,0:07:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.95,0:07:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kirin's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.79,0:07:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kirin's Horn...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.50,0:07:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.38,0:07:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Open your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.47,0:07:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.63,0:07:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.55,0:07:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why aren't the lights back on!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.14,0:07:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.93,0:07:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.60,0:07:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Kid come?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.10,0:07:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.07,0:07:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kirin's Horn...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:07:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The four keys are still pinned to the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.37,0:08:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How in the world did...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.12,0:08:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know yet how he did it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.08,0:08:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the approximately one minute long blackout...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.50,0:08:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He, or his accomplice, ran around in the dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.13,0:08:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And got to the four pedestals with the keyholes, that much is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.01,0:08:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.35,0:08:24.81,title01,,0,0,0,,{\t(0,2460,\fs22)\xbord10\ybord5\be50\blur5}I have obtained the Kirin's horn\N \h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hKaitou Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid's card!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.01,0:08:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did he!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.31,0:08:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.48,0:08:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a card on this pedestal too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.06,0:08:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.65,0:08:33.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one here as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.11,0:08:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All four of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.36,0:08:38.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The breaker at the main temple was rigged.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.78,0:08:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blackout likely resulted from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like small time-bombs were set\Non all of the temple's storm windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That damn Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.71,0:08:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't just cause the blackout to create darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.38,0:09:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also blew out the windows to let the wind\Nand rain into cause such commotion...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.47,0:09:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And escaped during the confusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.68,0:09:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, take this youngster who\Nwas attacked by Kid to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring a car around!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.06,0:09:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And have the rest of the cars pursue Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.48,0:09:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this typhoon, he can't use his hang\Nglider, so he couldn't have gotten very far!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.82,0:09:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the report that just arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.07,0:09:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to a landslide, the roads are closed!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.66,0:09:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, if that youngster was given poison or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.08,0:09:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, a stun gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.75,0:09:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems as if Edogawa-kun was knocked out using this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy took out this lad, his toughest opponent, first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.97,0:09:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.14,0:09:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't "I see" me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all because you made a huge fuss to the\Nmedia about that jewel you found last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You provoked that guy before you had a proper security detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.78,0:10:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a month ago that I heard that the magnificent piece of\Namber known as "Kirin's Horn" was sleeping in this temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.99,0:10:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I purposely delayed the announcement\Nuntil I had obtained ownership of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.25,0:10:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The premise that this senile fool had gotten caught up in\Nthe moment of having found bait to hook him with...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that yours truly foolishly challenged him to a duel without\Nhaving arranged a sufficient security force — was actually planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:31.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, these lights that seem hastily affixed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.97,0:10:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was aware those could be manipulated to cause a blackout.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.77,0:10:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I already noticed the stupid trick he set up on the storm windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.15,0:10:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weak electricity running through the four\Npedestals, and calling the Detective Boys here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.70,0:10:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all part of the scheme to confuse and\Nentice him into coming to this musty old temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.08,0:10:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wood on the windows that looks rotted and easily broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.83,0:10:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the wall that looks like a single strike could knock it down...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.54,0:11:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They have steel inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.21,0:11:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, on the two doors that serve as entrances and\Nexits, I set up locking mechanisms and hid sensors in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.55,0:11:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're designed so if they're forced\Nopen, a piercing alarm will go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we didn't hear that sound, it must mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.77,0:11:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Kaitou Kid and any of his accomplices...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.94,0:11:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are still here, that's what!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.07,0:11:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Inspector Nakamori...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.71,0:11:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Other than the children, go ahead and pinch everyone's face...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.47,0:11:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that, there's something I want you to clear up for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.34,0:11:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did Kid steal that amber horn from the Kirin statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.10,0:12:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the blackout, you nailed the white,\Nblack, red, and green keys to the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in the four corners of the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.98,0:12:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are white, black, red, and green pedestals with keyholes, which\Nthe keys needed to be put into and turned at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.91,0:12:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise the statue of Kirin hidden in\Nthe central pillar shouldn't be revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.37,0:12:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if Kid somehow made spare copies of the keys...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.67,0:12:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could he accomplish that in the darkness, where\Nneither the pedestal nor the keyhole were visible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.42,0:12:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's just light, couldn't it have been the kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.05,0:12:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They have lights on their watches.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.60,0:12:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they said they'd protect the pedestals,\Nthat guy probably relied on their lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.64,0:12:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't turn on any lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.86,0:12:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true we were blocking the keyholes like this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.07,0:12:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara told us not to turn our lights on, even if the lights went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.32,0:12:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:12:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were blocking them, no one came?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.91,0:12:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This keyhole...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.42,0:13:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.59,0:13:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fluorescent paint!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.05,0:13:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.88,0:13:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This keyhole also has fluorescent paint!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.84,0:13:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.93,0:13:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I figured, there's fluorescent paint on the tips of all four keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.97,0:13:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably got there when they were put in the keyholes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.06,0:13:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, with just the tiniest bit of illumination on the keyholes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.36,0:13:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He handed the keys off to his accomplices in the darkness, who put\Nthem into the lit keyholes and turned them at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.24,0:13:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And thus Kirin's Horn was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.95,0:13:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.12,0:13:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitou Kid-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.87,0:13:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.54,0:13:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an obvious fact that the keys Kid used\Nweren't copies, but these keys right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.05,0:13:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means you purposely nailed the metal hook\Nholding the keys with little force for easy access...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.01,0:14:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after using the keys, you returned\Nthem to the wall - the only possibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.06,0:14:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you try pulling the hook off?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.81,0:14:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They aren't so easily moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.90,0:14:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You simply secured them better after use, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.99,0:14:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going to go that far, then just search me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.62,0:14:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all if I'm Kid, then I should have Kirin's Horn on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.87,0:14:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, even if you hadn't suggested it, I was planning on doing th—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.67,0:14:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.04,0:14:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not allow the Detective Boys to conduct the searches?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.09,0:14:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the inspector and advisor are Kid and his accomplice...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.34,0:14:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's the possibility you could rig the search to deceive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.39,0:14:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can relax if it's us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.43,0:14:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way we could be Kid's accomplices!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.48,0:14:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.52,0:14:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though, we'll also search everyone else, is that OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Due to certain circumstances, we will\Nbe switching to another program.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.99,0:15:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We apologize for the wait."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.79,0:15:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scrolling ticker has been saying that for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not starting at all, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I wonder what that strange sound was?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was hard on the ears, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:16.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a sound like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.35,0:15:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.10,0:15:30.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite the fact you've searched everyone here, are\Nyou saying you still couldn't locate the Kirin's Horn?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.52,0:15:34.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We figured it may have been slipped onto us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.44,0:15:39.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we even checked our own clothes and Edogawa-kun's\Npockets, but nothing came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.82,0:15:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The space between the window bars is such that Kirin's Horn can't be\Npushed through, so even if he had an accomplice on the outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.41,0:15:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't have been able to pass it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.00,0:15:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As—I—said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid has already escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and open the doors so we can chase after him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.09,0:15:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:15:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the sought-after jewel is gone, it's\Nnatural to think Kid wouldn't still be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.18,0:16:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.35,0:16:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why he had to knock out Kudou-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.44,0:16:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, taking out a bothersome opponent would\Nbe considered an overwhelming victory, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.36,0:16:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you merely put them to sleep, you won't get\Nthe satisfaction of rubbing it in their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.83,0:16:27.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there some other reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.50,0:16:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What also bothers me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.29,0:16:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Samizu Kichiemon's statement carved into this pillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.29,0:16:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One who desires to acquire Kirin without depending on\Nthe correct method must devote themselves to changing."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.93,0:16:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, those who want to get Kirin's\NHorn without following the right steps...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.35,0:16:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Must go with the flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.85,0:16:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The correct method likely refers to the keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.06,0:16:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what is the "flow"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.15,0:16:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.61,0:16:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flow of the wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.36,0:17:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.65,0:17:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the wind's coming in is\Nbecause Kid broke the storm windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did Kid open the windows in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he already caused a blackout, there's no point\Nin further confusing us with the wind and rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if Inspector Nakamori is right and that Advisor Suzuki is Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.38,0:17:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd have to take off the keys affixed to\Nthe wall within a minute in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.10,0:17:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Handing them off to accomplices without any light...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.02,0:17:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turning the keys at the same time without a signal...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.06,0:17:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And making the stolen jewel disappear\Nas if by magic, is it even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, whether or not Kid even had any accomplices is doubtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.78,0:17:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calling a number of accomplices to this locked room...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a chance that one of them may get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.91,0:17:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd definitely avoid a risk like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.75,0:17:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not good at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.42,0:17:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd definitely say something like this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.59,0:18:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You can't even figure out something this elementary?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a sparrow, you'd chirp and chatter...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.22,0:18:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that vast knowledge of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sparrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.94,0:18:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About this paragraph...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.94,0:18:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the word "sparrow" could be a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.02,0:18:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of it has faded, but the kanji for\N"sparrow" is carved in that red pedestal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.53,0:18:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red sparrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.66,0:18:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzaku!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.00,0:18:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.42,0:18:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see the kanji for "sparrow" on top of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.92,0:18:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe there was a sparrow statue attached to the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.26,0:18:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a sparrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Red" could be "vermilion".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.56,0:18:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the faded word above the kanji "sparrow" had been "vermilion"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:18:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would form the name of a legendary\Ncreature among the four Divine Beasts...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.81,0:18:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzaku, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.87,0:19:01.87,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(460,0)\blur5\fscy120\fscx120}Suzaku\N{\fscy85\fscx85}Vermilion Bird
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzaku is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something you see in games...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.86,0:19:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A red bird like a phoenix?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.53,0:19:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And facing the red pedestal on the right\Nside, the white pedestal must be for...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.66,0:19:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Byakko.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.88,0:19:18.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(460,0)\blur5\fscy120\fscx120}Byakko\N{\fscy85\fscx85}White Tiger
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.92,0:19:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And further to the right is this black pedestal for...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genbu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:25.64,Character Card,,0,10,0,,{\fad(460,0)\blur5\fscy120\fscx120}Genbu\N{\fscy85\fscx85}Black Tortoise
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Further to the right again, the green pedestal that\Nis also to the left of the red pedestal earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no denying that a statue of Seiryuu had been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.23,0:19:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't Seiryuu written as "azure dragon"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That pedestal's color is green, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.16,0:19:51.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The kanji for "azure" was originally used to represent the\Ncolor of plants as seen in lush mountains and trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.71,0:19:54.50,Character Card,,125,0,0,,{\fad(460,0)\blur5\fscy120\fscx120}Seiryuu\N{\fscy85\fscx85}Azure Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:54.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Seiryuu's original color was actually meant to be green.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.33,0:19:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The four divine beasts each have a direction they protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzaku is the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.50,0:20:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Byakko is the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.92,0:20:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genbu is the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.59,0:20:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Seiryuu is the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in the center location would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Kirin, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, this paragraph written by Samizu\NKichiemon at the bottom of this pillar is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "aftercare" or backup plan in case the keys are lost or stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.61,0:20:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "one who desires to acquire Kirin without\Ndepending on the correct method" refers to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.36,0:20:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who want to get Kirin's Horn without using the keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next part, the "changing" from "must\Ndevote themselves to changing" means...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flow of time or the changing of places.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.04,0:20:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the "devote themselves" part, we probably can\Ntake it to mean "to go with the flow and let it be."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.51,0:20:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, by just waiting and not doing anything,\Nthe Kirin would appear from the pillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.26,0:21:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the four pedestals in the corners of this room\Nare Suzaku, Byakko, Genbu, and Seiryuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.69,0:21:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it have something to do with the\Ncolors and directions that each represents?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.82,0:21:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it may be asking us to perform some action in\Naccordance with a particular order for the four pedestals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.45,0:21:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But colors don't have any order.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:18.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe it has something to do with\Nthe order of east, west, south and north?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.41,0:21:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we say "east-north region" here in\NJapan, so shouldn't north come after east?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.21,0:21:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think the order should start with north!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.46,0:21:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since north is on the top in all maps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.97,0:21:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like we can't decide on an order going by only directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be it going clockwise or counter-clockwise,\Nthey will still flow continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.85,0:21:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.10,0:21:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only Suzaku, Byakko, Genbu, and Seiryuu had an\Norder attached to them, it might have worked...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.94,0:21:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet Conan-kun would know something, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.82,0:21:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been sleeping like that the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.57,0:21:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, as far as revealing the\NKirin statue from the pillar goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.91,0:22:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be done by either inserting the four keys into the\Nfour pedestal keyholes and turning at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.62,0:22:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or without the keys, by doing something to the four pedestals in\Nsome kind of order - there doesn't seem to be any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.42,0:22:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kid doing that during the one\Nminute blackout seems impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.13,0:22:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had accomplices, there had to be some sort of a signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.51,0:22:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So let's first determine that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.68,0:22:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can we determine that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.27,0:22:23.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.73,0:22:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The people who filmed the evidential VTR...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.98,0:22:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The TV crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.15,0:22:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.70,0:22:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until you open your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.91,0:22:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rest of us will have no choice but to do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.41,0:24:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it was supposed to be a young staff member...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.83,0:24:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going this far, then you're suspicious too, cameraman!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.83,0:24:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't sleep forever, just lend us some knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.63,0:24:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,White...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.88,0:24:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remove the lock from that door at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.38,0:24:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.22,0:24:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Magician in the Moonlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.80,0:24:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.87,0:24:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta's 10-Yen-Sized Bald Spot
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.89,0:24:49.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,Pun on pronounciation\Nof "bald" and "bold"
